_Two_Alter", "agent_output": "def is_Two_Alter(s: str) -> bool:\n    # Check if string length is less than 2, it can't be alternating\n    if len(s) < 2:\n        return False\n    \n    # Extract unique characters\n    unique_chars = set(s)\n    \n    # If there are not exactly two unique characters, return False\n    if len(unique_chars) != 2:\n        return False\n    \n    # Check if characters alternate\n    for i in range(len(s) - 1):\n        if s[i] == s[i + 1]:\n            return False\n    \n    return True\n\n# Verification of the assertions\nassert is_Two_Alter(\"abab\") == True\nassert is_Two_Alter(\"aaaa\") == False\nassert is_Two_Alter(\"xyz\") == False"}
